==English==
===Etymology===
The [[police officer]] sense is from the [[surname]] of '''[[w:Robert Peel|Sir Robert Peel]]''', who [[establish]]ed [[London]]'s [[police]] force.  The other senses are [[peel]] + [[-er]].

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-iːlə(r)|-iːlə(r)]]

====Noun====
{{en-noun-reg}}
#A person whose [[job]] it is to [[peel]] [[fruit]] or [[vegetable]] [[produce]].
#A [[utensil]] for peeling fruit or vegetables.
#:''potato peeler''
#{{UK}} {{slang}} {{archaic}} A [[police officer]].
#A woman (or less commonly a man) who removes her cloting for entertainment. A [[stripper]].

